FBIS3-55004 "drsov003_t_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Meri Criticism of Yeltsin's Comments Reported PM0401132594 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 4 Jan 94 p 1 PM0401132594 Moscow PRAVDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Report from the PRAVDA, ITAR-TASS column: "Estonian President Unhappy"] [Text] Estonian President L. Meri has sharply criticized B. Yeltsin's New Year address, in which the Russian president advocated that the interests of the 25 million Russian citizens living in the republics of the former Soviet Union be better protected. In an interview with AP, Meri claimed in particular that: "The words and tone used by Yeltsin could be evidence of how weak democratic forces in Russia are. So Russia has chosen the path of utilizing the aggressive policy typical of the former USSR."
